Fear of not being appreciated
It is easy to forget this by the time you grow up, but in the early years of your life when you remember things, you are in a situation where you cannot survive without food, clothing, and shelter provided by a creature many times bigger and stronger than you, and at this time you acquire [anxiety] that "if you are not [appreciated], you will die".

Sometimes this anxiety is not resolved in adulthood.
For example, a person with a stronger [need for power] who takes pleasure in controlling others will try to control others by taking hold of their reputation. Insecurity can be encouraged and reinforced by these people.

---

What would it take to antidote the anxiety of "I'll die if I'm not appreciated?"
　Proposal 1: A quantity of property that others can live without having to value it.
　　It's called [economic independence].

---

[The basic personality of a person established in childhood].
　The word structure "is" gives a strong nuance of "something that is established and difficult to change," but the general direction is the same.
　Formed in childhood, it will affect your life as an adult.
